./.title: Introduction
./.body: All the documentation related to views

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/structu.title: Get a structure from a template
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/structu.body:
Reload previous structures in the molecule editor
The structure editor remembers the last 20 edited structures. If you want to start your new molecule from a previous one you may simply click on the history icon.

A list showing the last edited structures will appear and you should just click on one of them to use it as a template.

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/binap/.title: Chirality of BINAP derivatives
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/binap/.body:
BINAP and axial chirality
The chemical structure editor (openchemlib) allows to specify the axial chirality of molecules for which rotation around a single bond is blocked.
To specify the chirality you need to add a chiral bond on a single-bond that is next to the chiral bond.

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfGroup.title: Molecular formula: groups
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfGroup.body:
Molecular formula: using groups
While the molecular formula is calculated automatically from the chemical structure it is sometimes useful to directly edit the molecular formula.
In the editor you are allowed to use groups like Ala, Me, ...

The full list of allowed groups can be seen by clicking on the little grid icon.

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfParen.title: Molecular formula: parenthesis
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfParen.body:
Molecular formula: parenthesis
While the molecular formula is calculated automatically from the chemical structure it is sometimes useful to directly edit the molecular formula.
The mass editor allows to use as many parenthesis level as you want.

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfIsoto.title: Molecular formula: isotopes
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfIsoto.body:
Molecular formula: isotopes
While the molecular formula is calculated automatically from the chemical structure it is sometimes useful to directly edit the molecular formula.
Isotopes have to be entered between square brackets like [13C]. There is one exception, D that is a synonym of [2H].

There is also the possibility to enter non natural isotopic ratio. In this case the ratio between all the stable isotopes will be placed between curly brackets and separated by a comma. ie if you have a molecule with 10 carbons having 20% [12C] and 80% [13C] you will enter C{20,80}10.

15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfSalt/.title: Molecular formula: salt
15c9a2dcd55c963fdedf2c18a1471b03/mfSalt/.body:
Molecular formula: salt and multiple components
While the molecular formula is calculated automatically from the chemical structure it is sometimes useful to directly edit the molecular formula.
You may enter a multipart molecular formula by separating all the parts by a ..
The monoisotopic mass as well as the molecular weight will be calculated correctly.

2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/ionizat.title: Ionizations
2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/ionizat.body:
Ionizations
In order to observe a neutral molecule the mass spectrometer will charge it using different techniques. This may involve adding protons, remove electrons, etc
You can also observe charged molecules resulting of the addition of Na+, K+, etc.
In order to evaluate all the possibilities you must enter in the 'ionizations' field a comma separated list of all the allowed ionizations.
You may as well specify multiple charges. Here are some examples of allowed patterns:

H+ (addition a proton)
H+, Na+, K+ (either a proton, sodium cation or potassium cation)
H+, (H+)2, (H+)3 (addition of one, two or three protons)
(H+)-1, (H+)-2, (H+)-3 (removal of one, two or three protons)

2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/unsatur.title: Filter by unsaturation
2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/unsatur.body:
Filter by unsaturation
This tools search for possible molecular formula based on:

a monoisotopic experimental mass
one or many ionization possibilities

The result can be further filtered by the degree of unsaturation.
For stable molecules the unsaturation degree is expected to be greater or equal to zero.
Moreover if it is non radical molecule the unsaturation degree is integer.

Please note that those filters apply on the molecular formula without the ionization.

2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/peakPic.title: Select a monoisotopic mass
2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/peakPic.body:
Entering a monoisotopic mass
When loading an experimental spectrum the tool will automatically make a peak picking (centroid) that will be displayed on the spectrum.
Zooming in the spectrum will progressively add more and more detailed peaks.
If you are searching the molecular formula of an unknown products you should click on the label corresponding to the monoisotopic experimental mass.

2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/results.title: Understanding the result table
2294a250c8c1da87ca6753a6eb93c166/results.body:
Results table
This tool calculates on-the-fly the possible molecular formula based on a monoisotoipc mass and possible ionizations.
The resulting table will contain green background lines if this molecular formula exists in PubChem. This is an excellent way to find plausible molecular formula of unknown products.

The results contains various columns:

the NON-IONIZED molecular formula
the monoisotopic mass of the NON-IONIZED molecule
the unsaturation degree
the ionization
the observed mass
the total charge (with ionization)
the error in mDa
the absolute value of the error in ppm

4c986ed7d921b11fbe6f20240f0df3a8/viewPar.title: View any acquisition parameters
4c986ed7d921b11fbe6f20240f0df3a8/viewPar.body:
Visualize all acquisition and processing parameters
An icon is present in the list of experimental spectra that allows to display and search for any acquisition and processing parameters.

After clicking on this icon you will get a list of the parameters with a search box that allows to filter the list by parameter name.

a7448bb6798371144f9a5ecab184e100/upload/.title: Upload IR spectra
a7448bb6798371144f9a5ecab184e100/upload/.body:
Upload IR spectra
You can upload an IR spectrum in 3 different ways:

by drag and drop
by clicking on the upload zone and selecting the file
by copying the spectrum in the clipboard and make a CTRL+V (or âŒ˜+V on OsX).

The format of the file should be a jcamp (extension .dx or .jdx) that is a usual
exportation format on all the IR spectrophotometer.
